{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":271119,"duration_api_ms":270276,"num_turns":6,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"3284fbf1-e0ca-4b84-8e90-edf470fc37ec","total_cost_usd":0.7082482999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":32050,"cache_read_input_tokens":197132,"output_tokens":2941,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":32050,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":2941,"cacheReadInputTokens":197132,"cacheCreationInputTokens":32050,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.37243850000000006,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":233,"outputTokens":16755,"cacheReadInputTokens":1452493,"cacheCreationInputTokens":85242,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.3358098000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"After examining model.rs, fs.rs, and service.rs in detail, I agree with the planner on all six amendments. The three targeted removals (milestone_id optionality, legacy parsing, backward-compat tests) are well-justified by the acceptance criteria and confirmed by code inspection showing milestone_id is always set at write time. The _started_at removal is correctly rejected because the parameter is needed for the start-attempt matching fix. The broad c6ca5e53 amendment is correctly rejected because run_id, plan_hash, and outcome_detail are legitimately None in actual write paths. The start-attempt matching fix addresses a real correctness issue visible in the test at service.rs:3179-3235.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-14-b5a477a3","decision":"accept","rationale":"Code inspection confirms milestone_id is always available at write time: record_task_run_start sets it explicitly (fs.rs:2862), and append_task_run sets it via canonicalize_entry_for_write (fs.rs:2577). With no legacy on-disk data, making it a required String eliminates the backfill in read_task_runs_from_path (fs.rs:2556-2558) and the canonicalize_entry_for_write workaround. This tightens the schema correctly and ensures malformed writes fail fast."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-c5bceaec","decision":"accept","rationale":"The parse_legacy function (fs.rs:2289-2321) handles a comma-delimited format that was never written to disk by this new feature. The legacy branch in repairable_completion_event (fs.rs:2449-2459) silently replaces malformed data instead of rejecting it. Since render_completion_journal_details writes structured JSON, the only valid parse path is the JSON one. Removing parse_legacy and the legacy repair branch eliminates dead code and ensures serialization bugs surface immediately."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-1ac821d9","decision":"accept","rationale":"The test task_run_entry_backward_compat_without_new_fields (service.rs:1232-1245) validates deserialization of JSON missing milestone_id/run_id/plan_hash/outcome_detail — behavior that should no longer be supported once milestone_id is made required. The read_task_runs_backfills_milestone_id_for_legacy_entries test (service.rs:1247-1282) validates the backfill logic being removed by fr-14-b5a477a3. These tests would either fail or test dead paths after the other amendments land. The skipped_beads test caveat (only remove if that field is separately made required) is appropriately scoped."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-89e13c37","decision":"reject","rationale":"While _started_at is currently unused in find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:421), amendment fr-14-ec2442bd correctly identifies that started_at is the missing discriminator for distinguishing retries from replays. Removing the parameter now would require re-adding it to implement the matching fix. The parameter exists because it should be used — the bug is that it isn't, not that it's present."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-c6ca5e53","decision":"reject","rationale":"This amendment conflates milestone_id (always known at write time) with run_id, plan_hash, and outcome_detail (legitimately unknown at some write paths). Code inspection shows: run_id and plan_hash are passed as Option<&str> and can be None in record_task_run_start (fs.rs:2865-2866); outcome_detail is always None at start time (fs.rs:2868) and only set during completion. Making all these fields required would break valid writes. The valid parts of this amendment (milestone_id, legacy journal repair) are already covered by fr-14-b5a477a3 and fr-14-c5bceaec with better precision."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-ec2442bd","decision":"accept","rationale":"The test at service.rs:3179-3235 demonstrates the bug: a legacy open attempt (run_id=None) is left permanently in Running state as a phantom row when a new named retry arrives. find_matching_running_task_run ignores started_at entirely (model.rs:416-442), so it cannot distinguish a genuine new retry from an idempotent replay of the same attempt. This creates incorrect audit trails in both directions. Using started_at as the discriminator — combined with keeping the parameter per the fr-14-89e13c37 rejection — fixes attempt identity without over-constraining the schema."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"9e6f75a7-1b74-42ec-bd9d-f9f0d84720e7"}
